sentence: Looking at options trading activity among components of the Russell 3000 index, there is noteworthy activity today in Salesforce.com Inc (Symbol: CRM), where a total volume of 28,440 contracts has been traded thus far today, a contract volume which is representative of approximately 2.8 million underlying shares (given that every 1 contract represents 100 underlying shares).
That number works out to 55% of CRM's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 5.2 million shares.
Particularly high volume was seen for the $150 strike put option expiring October 19, 2018 , with 6,491 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 649,100 underlying shares of CRM.

WD-40 Co (Symbol: WDFC) saw options trading volume of 328 contracts, representing approximately 32,800 underlying shares or approximately 52.6% of WDFC's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 62,340 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $140 strike put option expiring November 16, 2018 , with 126 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 12,600 underlying shares of WDFC.

That number of contracts represents approximately 186,100 underlying shares, working out to a sizeable 51.9% of LGIH's average daily trading volume over the past month, of 358,685 shares.
Especially high volume was seen for the $40 strike put option expiring October 19, 2018 , with 753 contracts trading so far today, representing approximately 75,300 underlying shares of LGIH.
